commitResults.messageTitle: Update Milo Ice messages for better user experience
commitResults.messageBody:
Milo Ice uses certain phrases in error and normal messages that is less
user-friendly.

Improving the wording of messages enhances clarity, provides a better
user experience and makes interactions feel more natural.

Revise and refine the chatbot’s error messages and normal responses to
be clearer, friendlier and more informative.

Ensuring messages are well-structured and intuitive helps users
understand issues.

This update does not affect the chatbot's logic or functionality,
only the displayed text changes.

commitResults.messageTitle: Ensure start time is before end time in Event
commitResults.messageBody:
The Event class currently allows invalid time ranges where the start
time is the same as or after the end time. Rescheduling also does not
follow this rule.

Add a validation check to enforce that the start time must be before
the end time. Throw an exception if the condition is violated.

This ensures event data remains consistent and prevents scheduling
errors.

Currently, the README.md has wrong title and lacks clear instructions
on how to use key features of Milo Ice.

Update the README.md by adding explanations, examples, and command
formats.

This helps introduce Milo Ice to new user and help them learn the key
features quickly.

commitResults.messageTitle: Improve the GUI and remove Ui.java
commitResults.messageBody:
Ui.java currently only prints messages to the terminal,
which is no longer necessary.

Remove Ui.java and refactor code to rely solely on the graphical
interface. Also tweak the CSS code to change the GUI appearance.

This change eliminates redundant code and ensures all user interactions
happen through the GUI.

No functionality is lost, as all relevant messages are now handled
within the GUI components.

commitResults.messageTitle: Correct MainWindow.fxml filename from MainWIndow.fxml to resolve JAR loading issue
commitResults.messageBody:
The JAR file is failing to load `MainWindow.fxml` because `FXMLLoader`
is case-sensitive and cannot find `view/MainWindow.fxml` due to a naming
mismatch.

The filename needs to be corrected because JAR resources are
case-sensitive and the incorrect casing causes runtime error.

Rename `MainWIndow.fxml` to `MainWindow.fxml` to match the expected
resource path in the code.

This is done to prevent `getResource()` from returning `null`.

No other changes were made, and the fix should resolve the issue without
affecting functionality.
